The social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
The changes provide for the preservation of travel in public passenger transport.
Since September 24, the procedure for organizing preferential travel of citizens using a social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region has been changing.
According to the press service of the Russian government in the Ivanovo region, the changes provide for the preservation of benefits for travel in public passenger transport and bring the scheme of settlements on the social card in accordance with the requirements of the Federal Law No. 161 of the Federal Law "On the National Payment System."
At the same time, the social card of a resident of the Ivanovo region is recognized as an electronic means of payment.
Accordingly, the conditions of its application change.
So, the replenishment limit is set now not on trips, as before, but in the amount of money, with the preservation of winter and summer periods - in winter no more than 400 rubles, in the summer - no more than 800 rubles for the current month.
Now the holders of the social card on the receipts issued in the transport will need to track not the number of remaining trips, but the balance of money.
The cost of preferential travel for citizens will be 1/2 tariff, valid for the carrier.
The remaining half of the fare is reimbursed by the regional budget.
The schedule of replenishment of the social card with funds remains the same - in the period from the 24th of the previous month to the 23rd day of the current month.
The new order of travel on the social map will have a number of advantages.
So, it is possible to keep a detailed record of the expenditure of funds on the social card with accuracy to the pennies.
In addition, it is possible to return the enrolled, but unspent funds.
We also add that the scheme of settlements with carriers becomes transparent, as now half of the fare is paid by the citizen, and the same amount is reimbursed to the carrier.
No commission will be charged when depositing funds on the card.
In turn, Vasily Silkin, deputy head of the Department of Roads and Transport of the Ivanovo region, said that in 2014 more than 33 million trips using a social card were made in the region, and almost 25 million trips in 2015.
In the regional budget for the provision of preferential travel of citizens using a social card, more than 470 million rubles are provided.
As of September 1, the amount of compensation for these purposes amounted to more than 312 million rubles.
