Experts criticize the review of e-cigarettes from Public Health England
The government-funded agency's claims that e-cigarettes are 95% less harmful than smoking were at a meeting of 12 people, some of whom are linked to the tobacco industry, the researchers said.
Experts published in the British Medical Journal (BMJ) together with Lancet criticized the evidence used by Public Health England (PHE) in its e-cigarette report.
