This year, the study of the Association of Russian Managers "Top-1000 Russian managers" is published for the 16th time.
As a tool for assessing the professional reputation of Russian managers of the highest echelon, the study sums up the work of Russian managers for the year, identifying leaders in industries and functional areas.
The initial pool of candidates consists of the winners of the rating last year.
The winners of the last year are invited to confirm their participation as a candidate of the rating of the current year and nominate members of their management team.
In addition, each of the candidates on the original list is proposed to nominate up to 10 new managers from other companies, which would be appropriate to add to the general pool of candidates.
It is possible to nominate the following heads of the functional areas of the company: CFO, Commercial Director, Marketing Director, HR Director, CIO, Director of Public and Corporate Relations, Director of Relations with Authorities, Director of Corporate Governance.
Each expert-proposed manager is sent an invitation to participate in the rating and is given the opportunity to nominate his management team and up to ten new managers from other companies.
Nomination of candidates on the industry principle is carried out on the basis of the industry classifier of the Association of Managers: information technology, commercial banks, forest and forestry, mechanical engineering, media business, metallurgy, multidisciplinary holdings, professional services, telecommunications, service and production of consumer goods, insurance, construction, trade, transport, financial sector, pharmaceuticals, chemical industry, energy and fuel complex.
Each participant is provided with a login and password to enter the site www.top1000.amr.ru, where they see information about the rest of the participants and can make their assessments on the criteria proposed for each functional direction.
The methodology for the construction of the rating is the principle of "The best choose the best": top managers evaluate top managers, functional managers evaluate functional managers.
Such a principle allows you to get the most authentic assessment of the professional reputation of colleagues.
The final results of the rating are approved at the meetings of expert commissions.
To the full-time meetings of expert commissions, all willing candidates of the rating of the current year and multiple candidates of the rating of previous years are invited.
The commissions are organized on a functional basis: a commission for approval of the list of senior heads and eight commissions for approval of heads of functional areas.
At the meetings of the expert commissions, it is proposed to approve the lists submitted in alphabetical order (the places are stored strictly according to the Internet assessment and are closed information until the rating is published) or make actualizing their adjustments according to the attached list of reserve candidates.
The names of the companies are given in accordance with the rules of the Russian language and the norms of "Kommersant."
At the time of publication of the rating, changes in the status of managers and companies are possible.
The comfortable rate for the investment loan is 10-13%.
According to experts, the market of lending to small and medium-sized businesses in January-April of this year fell by 40%.
What do you estimate the situation today?
After the panic of the end of 2014 - the beginning of 2015, the volume of lending to SMEs decreased significantly.
The reason is clear: a sharp increase in interest rates.
Lending at 25-30% per annum was not beneficial to anyone.
If earlier the bank could put in a higher rate all its possible problems in the future, from delays to non-refunds, now it is impossible to do: the rates are already sky-high.
For business, the current level of interest rates on SME loans is uncomfortable.
For a significant part of investment projects, the current level is unacceptable in terms of their payback.
The rate level of 10-13% would allow the business to invest in a wide range of projects and form an attractive profitability on them.
How much, according to your estimates, is the demand of entrepreneurs for loans?
After the depreciation of the Central Bank, the situation has improved a little.
Credit resources are more accessible.
However, according to our observations, customers began to apply for loans much less often.
First of all, business does not understand the prospects for its development and future income.
Today, there is one way out for business: it is necessary to learn how to work, focusing on today's economic situation in the country and the region.
It is necessary to monitor the current results more closely, to monitor the movement of cash.
At the same time, in the presence of financial resources, it is worth using new technologies that allow to modernize the equipment, reduce the cost of production and energy supply.
All this, ultimately, allows the company to make the products more competitive and keep the business even in an unstable economic situation.
What are the main trends in the SME lending market will strengthen and affect its development by the end of 2015?
Will the interest rate change?
The forecast for the reduction of the average rate will largely depend on the policy of the Central Bank, and now the regulator demonstrates consistency in the issue of lowering the key rate.
However, a radical drop in the price of loans for SMEs should not be expected.
In the current situation, the problem is primarily inflation, which makes an increased interest rate necessary to generate real income.
In addition, the cost of money in Russia will remain high even with a decrease in the rates of the Central Bank.
If we talk about the level of delay, traditionally small and medium-sized businesses, limited both in the possibilities of replenishing funds and in options for correcting economic behavior, will certainly pose a greater risk to lenders.
I would not expect a significant reduction in the share of bad loans.
The main reason is international sanctions and their negative impact on the country's economy.
