The Duma introduced a bill on the indexation of social pensions, taking into account the increase in prices.
The state Duma introduced a bill providing for the indexation of social pensions annually from February 1, taking into account the increase in prices.
The author of the document - the deputy from "Fair Russia" Alexander Lomakin-Romyantsev - also proposes to carry out an additional indexation of pensions on April 1, if the growth rate of the subsistence minimum exceeds the growth rate of prices for goods and services.
Indexing of social pensions, according to the current legislation, is carried out annually from April 1, taking into account the growth rate of the subsistence minimum of the pensioner in the Russian Federation for the past year.
The draft law, introduced in the lower house, provides for the introduction of indexation of social pensions, taking into account the growth rate of consumer prices.
At the same time, the first indexation is postponed to February 1, and the second is held on April 1.
