Only satellite dishes, air conditioners on the walls and street lights remind you that you are not in the medieval, but in the modern city.
In the old part of the city preserved details of the water supply, built by the Persians about a thousand years ago.
To this day, ancient sources have reached, in which the locals still collect water.
Many Derbents prefer conventional tap water from the water from proven historical fountains.
In Derbent was one of the centers of pottery craft.
Polish and painted vases, dishes, jugs, cups were valued throughout the Caucasus.
The hands of the potters are now making wonderful ceramic products of both practical and souvenir purposes.
