The American Embassy in Russia expressed regret over the closure of the American center operating at the Library of Foreign Literature.
The center worked in Moscow for more than 22 years.
The U.S. Embassy in Moscow deeply regrets the unilateral decision of the Russian government to close the American center of the U.S. Embassy at the All-Russian State Library. M.I. Rudomino in Moscow.
"The unilateral steps taken by the Russian Federation in recent times cast doubt on the commitment of the Russian government to ties between the Russian and American peoples, which were not interrupted even during the Cold War and other difficult moments of the long history of relations between our countries," US Ambassador John Tefft said in a statement.
The American Center created deep and lasting connections between the people and culture of Russia and the United States.
It was the center of American culture, history and literature in the Russian capital, and also served as a meeting place with numerous American prominent figures, including cosmonauts, artists, athletes, scientists, politicians and writers.
"Last year alone, the American Center held more than 400 cultural and educational events and received more than 50,000 Russian visitors," the diplomat said.
Tefft recalled that about a year ago it was decided to close another joint Russian-American project - the FLEX (Future Leaders Exchange Program) educational exchange program.
